	faithHeading="Faith and the Bible in the Philippines"
	faithBodyHtml={`<p>The Philippines is the great stronghold of Christian faith in Asia. Roughly <strong>90% of Filipinos are Christian</strong> &mdash; the country has one of the largest Roman Catholic populations on earth and a fast-growing evangelical church, with about <strong>100 million believers</strong> in all.</p><p>Faith shapes everything: the fiestas, the family altars, the prayers whispered for loved ones working overseas. Filipinos widely read the Magandang Balita Biblia and Ang Biblia in Tagalog, alongside English Bibles.</p><p>And yet, for all this devotion, many Filipinos relate to God through ritual and obligation, and God can feel distant &mdash; especially for families stretched across oceans. The need is not a first faith. It is to know, in the Bible they already love, the Father who is always near.</p>`}
